manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: To beat the course, you need to know the course. With the compact Approach G30 GPS golf handheld and its full color mapping and touch targeting, victory is at hand. It easily slips into and out of your pocket or mounts nearly anywhere. It’s preloaded with more than 40,000 courses worldwide. Approach G30 Small but Powerful Handheld Golf GPS Sleek, compact handheld golf GPS with 2.3-inch color touchscreen display High-sensitivity GPS acquires satellites quickly to show distance to greens, hazards and doglegs Preloaded with more than 40,000 courses worldwide Full-color course mapping with Touch Targeting feature Green View allows you to place the pin in the correct location for the day, which improves distance accuracy

Keep It Handy The Approach G30 GPS golf device is compact so you can easily slip it into and out of your pocket, or take advantage of versatile mounting options to stash it nearly anywhere — including your belt, pull cart or golf bag — and easily slide it in and out with 1 hand.

Get More Courses Approach G30 comes with more than 40,000 preloaded courses worldwide, so you’re ready to play. You’ll see full-color maps of the entire course with CourseView, and with just a tap on the flag, you can zoom in on the green. Green View gives you its true orientation from wherever you are on the course. Record Your Round Digital scorecard makes it easy to keep scores for up to 4 players, and it automatically uploads to Garmin Connect when synced. And with stat tracking, you can keep track of putts, greens in regulation and fairways hit. Keep Playing With Approach G30, you’re always in touch. It displays smart notifications so you can get alerts from your phone for incoming calls, texts and emails. And it offers up to 15 hours of battery life on each charge for more time on the links. Improve Your Game Pair with the TruSwing golf swing analyzer, and you can train your swing with game-changing metrics, including swing speed and club path angles. By helping you understand what your swing is doing and how it impacts ball flight, you can improve your consistency on each stroke.

Precise Yardage Colorful layup arcs at 100, 150, 200 and even 250 yards let you know how far you need to hit when laying up. Touch Targeting lets you touch any point on the sunlight-readable display to get precise yardage to that spot — fairway, hazard, landing area or the front, middle and back of the green. Green View Shows you the true shape and layout of the green so you know where to aim. For even more precise targeting, you can touch and drag the pin to the day's placement. Stylish Design Sleek, compact GPS golf handheld offers a 2.3-inch touchscreen display for full-color mapping with Touch Targeting. Wireless Connectivity Receive emails, texts and alerts from your compatible smartphone right on your device, even if you’re in the middle of the fairway.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My golf game.
reviews.reviewText: It's accurate distance to the center of the green

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very Poor Owners Manual with Worse Customer Support
reviews.reviewText: The unit does what is supposed to done. Easy setup and intuitive stroke scoring. The manual gives no information as to how to track putts or fairways hit. When I contact customer service via chat, the rep had no idea how to set that feature up. Keep telling me how to records strokes. Second rep I reached a few hours later answered my question in about 30 seconds. Good unit. Bad manual, Questionable customer support.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Expensive but great tool.
reviews.reviewText: We had the forerunner of this that lasted for years. The updated version is even better with a brighter active touch screen. Seems to be accurate.The only objection is its smaller in overall size than the last one. (Screen size is about the same as older one.)But it does fit in your pocket or on your belt if desired.Still a 5 star item.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love the measuring feature in addition to pretty much all of it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Golf Aid
reviews.reviewText: Many more features that I need, but others would like them. I use primarily for distance readings to hazards or the green. Almost as accurate as my rangefinder, but faster and easier to use. In the golf cart, I keep it connected to the USB port. However, when in a rental cart, or when it is cart path only, the belt clip is great, and the battery is more than sufficient for 18 holes. I do not use the app.Well worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Does what you need
reviews.reviewText: Too large for me. I like the color graphics, but decided not to keep it. Went with a Golf Buddy watch instead.

reviews.reviewText: Easy to carry, very accurate and light weight. Haven't had any issues picking up golf courses in East coast.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Piece of junk
reviews.reviewText: Received it a couple days ago and used it for the first time today.I fully charged it. No problem there.Paired it to my smartphone. That worked fine.Connected to my computer and updated it. No problem.During the round it kept going to sleep. Had to restart several times which meant I couldn’t wait for it. Just had to take my shot.Each time it restarted I had to select the course again. All of the scores I had entered were gone. Had to enter them again.The last hole was a par 3 over water and this almost went in the water because I was so frustrated with it.Haven’t had a chance to see how it synced to the database.Also had a couple of times where I was standing at the 100 or 150 yard markers and it told me I was over 200 yards out.What a mistake buying this. It will be returned as soon as possible.
